info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued June 14 at 9:42AM CDT until June 14 at 11:00AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM CDT THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Visibility one quarter to one half mile in dense fog. * WHERE...Carlton and South St. Louis County. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Fond du Lac Band. * WHEN...Until 11 AM CDT this morning. * IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Dense fog is most likely in the elevated areas around the Twin Ports, including the Interstate 35 corridor between Duluth and Cloquet and the US Highway 53 corridor between Duluth and Independence.
info.instruction: If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.
